metadata.name: Mountain Moves #35
metadata.description:
Mountain Moves - ...kind of the logical real-time consequence of "Mountain View"
featuring different mountain formation (noise) types, different display modes
(outlines, semi outlines, no outlines, soft paint strokes)
6 color modes are still switchable. initially always 2-color modes.
on phones also uses device orientation.
 
 press 'c' ... switch color mode
 press 's' ... save png of actual resolution x3

metadata.name: Staircase #2
metadata.description:
Another year has begun. I love the boundaries of things. Like the border between years, the border between night and morning, day and night always fascinate us. When the year changes, I am certainly a different person than I was yesterday, but I am not sure that I have really changed. Am I really growing and changing for the better?
　It seems that the world does not always change for the better. I live in Japan, and in 2022 alone, there were many sad incidents. Every time I watch the news, I am disturbed. This is very sad.
　I am very, very small. I still don't know what kind of power I have, and even if I did, its impact on the world would be minute. I am building a staircase today. It is something that tries to see the boundary between something and something else, and connects them together so that they can come and go. The boundary will not be represented by a single line, but will be a vague gradation. Even with such uncertainty, I want to look at the heart of something that has changed or is about to change. I pray. I pray that even in the midst of so much sadness, there will be a little time for peace of mind. I pray that, as time goes by, we will be able to look at these sad events with a peaceful gaze. I want to build a staircase in my soul so that I can look through it.

metadata.name: Fragmented triacontahedron with iPhone 5s #24
metadata.description:
Title: Fragmented rhombic triacontahedron with model iPhone 5s
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of a plaster sculpture that has been deliberately shattered. A deconstructed 3d model of an iPhone 5s. Original photography, textures, screen captures and found images. Stream of consciousness text.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.

metadata.name: Random and Shapes #22
metadata.description:
Random is the most basic and essential tool in generative art. Yet with many different parameters, beautiful works could still be achievable with only random numbers.

This project is associated with a generative art course at NCCU in Taiwan.

metadata.name: a formal approach #20
metadata.description:
a field is generated, and filled with noise, then set aside.

a new field is generated.

a dotgrid (with occasional lines) is added.

a circle or square is drawn. 

a shader is applied; it relies on the noise field for randomization, and various values determine its output.

a border is applied, and a vignette is stippled.

the result is presented to the viewer, who can press "s" to save a 2000 x 2000 png. 

please note that there can some minor variation in how the preview is drawn versus how your computer renders the live view. (in general, this will be most obvious in the live view having more contrast.) this is an artifact of using a glsl shader for the majority of the view. the saved png output will be identical to the live view, however.

metadata.name: Impertailed #23
metadata.description:
A project that tries to test a lot of different forms of textures and lines, all together in a way to create something beautiful!

Happy New Year!
